results.name: Decimal expansion of the Dirichlet beta function of 5.
comment: The value of the Dirichlet L-series L(m=4,r=2,s=4), see arXiv:1008.2547.
reference: L. B. W. Jolley, Summation of Series, Dover (1961) eq. 308.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
formula: Equals 5*Pi^5/1536 = Sum_{n>=1} A101455(n)/n^5, where Pi^5 = A092731. [corrected by _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 01 2018]
maple: DirichletBeta := proc(s) 4^(-s)*(Zeta(0,s,1/4)-Zeta(0,s,3/4)) ; end proc: x := DirichletBeta(5) ; x := evalf(x) ;
mathematica: RealDigits[ DirichletBeta[5], 10, 105] // First (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Feb 20 2013, updated Mar 14 2018 *)
results.author: _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 15 2010
